Q1) Differentiate between JRE,JVM and JDK?

JRE (Java runtime environment);
it is helps to run JVM and java library it send code to JDK.
this JRE is present in all operating Systems
JVM(java virtual machine);
it is to convert java file to bytecode to execute in any operating System like Window,mac,linux
JDK(java Development kit);
JDK will run this java file in in all operating Systems.
JDK contains collection of frame works and library .it run combination of frame works and library